es for limiting, reforming, or eliminating life without parole sentences in the United States? Contributors explore the structure of life without parole sentences and the impact they have on prisoners, where the penalty fits in modern theories of punishment, and prospects for (as well as challenges to) reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCapital punishmentzUnited States. 0aLife imprisonmentzUnited States. 0aParolezUnited States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aBarkow, Rachel E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowers, Josh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapers, I. Bennett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolovich, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottschalk, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Jessica S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOgletree Jr., Charles J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOgletree, Charles J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobinson, Paul H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarat, Austin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarat, Austin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSimon, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814762493423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814762493.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  